                        "data": "Both full-time employees are entitled to 20 working days of paid time off (PTO) a year. A part-time employee is entitled to an annual holiday of at least 10 days. PTO accrues monthly at 1.667 days per month. Employees are eligible for full annual leave after 6 consecutive months of work."
